Cream Cheese Brownies
  --Cook's Illustrated

Filling:
4 oz cream cheese, cut into 8 pieces
1/2 c sour cream
2 tbsp sugar
1 tbsp ap flour

Microwave cream cheese until soft, 20-23 s. Add sour cream, sugar, and flour and whisk to combine. Set aside.

Brownie:
2/3 c (3 1/3 oz) ap flour
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
4 oz unsweetened chocolate, chopped fine
8 tbsp unsalted butter
1 1/4 c (8 3/4 oz) sugar
2 large eggs
1 tsp vanilla

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 325F. Make foil sling for 8" square baking pan, pushing foil into corners, smoothing foil flush; grease foil. Whisk flour, baking powder, and salt together in bowl and set aside. Microwave chocolate and butter in bowl at 50%, stirring occasionally, until melted, 1-2 min. Whisk sugar, eggs, and vanilla together in medium bowl. Add melted chocolate mixture and whisk until incorporated. Add flour mixture and fold to combine. Transfer 1/2 c batter to bowl used to melt chocolate. Spread remaining batter in prepared pan. Spread cream cheese filling evernly over batter. Microwave bowl of reserved batter until warm and pourable, 10-12 s. Using spoon, dollop softened batter over cream cheese filling, 6-8 dollops. Using knife, swirl batter through cream cheese filling, making marbled pattern, 10-12 strokes, leaving 1/2" border around edges. Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out with few moist crumbs attached, 35-40 min, rotating pan halfway through. Let cool in pan on wire rack for 1 hr. Using sling, lift brownies ouf pan, return to rack and let cool completely, ~1 hr. Cut into 2" squares and serve.
